			<div class="mxb">
				<div class="sh">
					Afghan opium production 'drops'
				</div>
			</div>
		</td>
		</tr>
    		
		
                <tr>
                    <td valign="top" width="416">
                        
	
		
                    	<font size="2">
		
			<!-- S BO -->
<!-- S IIMA -->
	
		<table cellspacing="0" align="right" border="0" width="203" cellpadding="0">
			<tr><td>
			<div>
				<img height="152" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0" width="203" alt="An Afghan opium farmer in his field" src="/web/20051029193957im_/http://newsimg.bbc.co.uk/media/images/41203000/jpg/_41203881_getty_poppy203.jpg" />
				<div class="cap">In 2004, Afghanistan produced 90% of the world's opium</div>
			</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		
	

	
<!-- E IIMA -->
<!-- S SF -->
<B>Afghanistan has registered a drop in the cultivation of opium for the first time since the fall of the Taleban, the United Nations says.</B>
<P>
The area under cultivation for opium has dropped by 21%, says the head of the UN Office for Drugs and Crime.
<P>
But the actual output has not changed much and Afghanistan is still the largest producer of opium in the world, accounting for almost 90% of supplies.
<P>
The opium poppy is the raw material for producing the drug heroin.
<!-- E SF -->
<P>
<P>
	<!-- S IINC --><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="203" align="right" border="0">
<tr>
	<td class="sibtbg">
	<div class="sih">QUICK GUIDE</div>
